I agree, had to reverse engineer the meaning from the test cases.

@2ndwolf: imagine a 6x7 rectangle, you can fill it with one 6x6 square and six 1x1 squares -> seven squares in total. But that's not optimal, you can fill it with one 4x4, two 3x3 and two 2x2 squares which leads to 5 squares in total as the minimum number to fill the rectangle.

I'd prefer something like "...integer sided squares..." or whatever, just a little more specific text would be nice but I really love that puzzle.
